# Build artifacts
target/
pkgconfig/

# Deliberately NOT ignored: output/tectonic_wasm.wasm (3.5 MB).
#
# It IS reproducible now — scripts/build-wasm.sh links successfully (BACKLOG #1
# is resolved), and this binary exports our `glyphx_*` ABI, so the e2e suite
# runs against it. It stays tracked for a different reason than before: the
# build needs emsdk plus a `-Z build-std` nightly-equivalent toolchain and takes
# tens of minutes, and deploy-web.yml runs `sync:engine` without building the
# engine. Untracked, every web deploy would either 404 or pay that build.
#
# Retire this exemption if deploy starts consuming a published artifact instead
# of the working tree.

# Deliberately NOT ignored: output/tectonic-bundle.tar.gz and output/packs/.
#
# Data inputs, not build outputs: they are assembled from a TeX Live install, so
# a clean machine cannot regenerate them and would be left unable to compile or
# test anything. deploy-web.yml runs `sync:engine` without a TeX Live, so an
# untracked bundle means a deployed editor that cannot compile, and untracked
# packs mean the pack feature silently vanishes in production — `loadPackIndex`
# returns null and no package set is ever offered.
#
# They change only when the TeX Live snapshot is refreshed or a pack is added,
# so they cost history size once rather than continuously. The packs are 0.5 MB
# in total, against 8.6 MB for the core bundle.
#
# Rebuild with:  pnpm engine:bundle (needs TeX Live; on Windows use WSL)

# OS
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
